  chips:[{k:'Market value',v:'\u20ac45.0m'},{k:'Fee',v:'\u00a352,000,000'},{k:'Contract',v:'to 2030 (Tottenham)'}],
  verdict:'The most progressive centre-back in the Premier League and arguably in Europe. Van Hecke does not just play out from the back: he actively dismantles defensive blocks with carries and line-breaking passes that the vast majority of centre-backs cannot replicate. Brighton agreeing a deal for 52 million pounds for a defender with one year left on his contract tells you everything about how the market rates him.',
  role:"Van Hecke operates as Brighton's primary ball-carrier out of defence, functioning almost as a third midfielder in possession phases. His willingness to drive through pressure invites fouls and repositions the team higher up the pitch with little risk, because he is composed enough to come out the other side of a challenge. He starts deep and aggressive as a sweeper when out of possession, then morphs into a creative outlet the moment his side regains the ball. Roberto De Zerbi's desire to reunite with him at Tottenham is no coincidence. The 3-4-3 and high-press systems that both coaches prefer are built around exactly his profile of ball-playing, press-resistant centre-back.",
